575 // ME+HE20220321
576 // Based on https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1666802/is-there-a-class-macro-in-c
577 // Get full formatted name of function
578 inline std::string aflowFunc(const std::string& pretty_func, const std::string& func) {
579  size_t end = pretty_func.find(func);
580  // Everything between the function name and the last space character
581  // are namespace and class name, if present
582  size_t begin = pretty_func.rfind(" ", end) + 1;
583  return XPID + pretty_func.substr(begin, end - begin) + func + "():";
584 }
585 
586 #define __AFLOW_FUNC__ aflowFunc(__PRETTY_FUNCTION__, __func__)

5110  //RF+SK20200410 START
5111  // Allen electronegativities were chosen for CCE since the IUPAC definition of oxidation states seems to use Allen electronegativities and since they also gave the best results
5112  // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxidation_state#Determination
5113  // since there were no Allen electronegativities available for f-elements besides Lu but these elements are usually very similar,
5114  // the Lu electronegativity was also used for the other f-elements listed (e.g. La)
5115  // this is confirmed by the Allred and Rochow electronegativities that are all very similar for all lanthanides
5116  double electronegativity_Allen; // https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/ja00207a003; https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/ja992866e; https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/ja9928677
